@sigmavirus24, for reference I have requests installed version 2.18.4. If I go into the init file and go to the if statement on line 9 and delete the text `requests.__version__` and replace it with `'2.18.4` then I no longer receive the error.

The variable `requests.__version__` should return '2.18.4' with type str() when called, but for some reason it is returning it as a variable with type module() instead of a variable with type str(). So when the '2.18.4' (type module()) is compared to the '2.0.0' (type str()) it returns a TypeError for comparing a `module()<str()`

This is solved by removing the `requests.__version__` and replacing it with `'2.18.4'` which is interpreted as a str() and then the type error goes away and the rest of the script runs successfully.

