> Are we supposed to perform a cast or is this an oversight in the C API? The documentation on those functions suggests the intent was to use rs2_sensor*
Yes. e.g:
```cpp
rs2_sensor* sensor = rs2_create_sensor(sensors, 0, &e);
int is_supported = rs2_supports_option((rs2_options*)sensor, RS2_OPTION_EXPOSURE, &e); 
```

It might be missing in the documentation but the `rs2_*option*` family of functions that takes a `rs2_options*`, can be used with either a sensor, or a `rs2_processing_block*`, e.g.:
```cpp
rs2_processing_block* colorizer = rs2_create_colorizer(&e);
int is_supported = rs2_supports_option((rs2_options*)colorizer, RS2_OPTION_COLOR_SCHEME, &e);
```
This was done from a C++ developer's point of view in order to support inheritance inside the library.
I will add the follow up tag to this, so we will remember to update our documentation (if it doesn't exist)

