1. If by "credis executable" you mean the new `redis-server` -- it's a redis fork that lives in @pcmoritz's repo -- the reason it's needed is because credis needs an private method of redis `getEventLoop()` to work.  (There are also some performance hacks but are minor.)   I gather from your second question that by "credis executable" you actually mean the `libmember.so`, then technically it is possible to merge code of course, but it'd be messy code bloat.

2. I don't know what you mean by that.  It's designed as a holistic solution.  It is possible -- and in fact, it is done so in this PR -- to disable replication and only supports the non-replicated 1-node case.

I managed to get a bootstrap 4 custom file input by subclassing the field method and providing a custom template:
`
class FileField(Field):
    template = "%s/layout/file_field.html"
`
Put the following template in your apps template folder in bootstrap4/layout/file_field.html (r change the path):
`
{% load crispy_forms_field %}
{% if field.is_hidden %}
    {{ field }}
{% else %}
        <div id="div_{{ field.auto_id }}" class="form-group{% if wrapper_class %} {{ wrapper_class }}{% endif %}">
            <div class="input-group">
                <div class="custom-file">
                  {% crispy_field field 'class' 'custom-file-input' %}
                  <label for="{{ field.id_for_label }}" class="custom-file-label">
                      {{ field.label|safe }}
                  </label>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
{% endif %}
`

Maybe this will help somebody create a fix.

